-- Toys "R" Us names executive vice president/COO
-- 
-- Fri Jun 1, 2007 9:59am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/06/01/us-toysrus-chiefoperatingofficer-idUSN0130898220070601

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Toys "R" Us Inc. on Friday said it has appointed a former acting CEO of RadioShack Corp. ( RSH.N ) to the newly created post of executive vice president, chief operating officer. 

 Claire Babrowski, 48, was named to oversee Toys "R" Us' worldwide logistics and information technology operations as well as oversee the toy retailer's global franchise operations. The appointment is effective immediately. Prior to RadioShack, she had a 30-year career at McDonald's Corp. ( MCD.N ) where she began as a part-time employee and left the restaurant company as senior executive vice president and chief restaurant operations officer. Toys "R" Us is owned by a consortium that includes Bain Capital Partners LLC, Kohlberg Kravis Roberts & Co. and Vornado Realty Trust ( VNO.N ).